Supercopa Libertadores 1997

Note: the worst three clubs in the first stage will not be admitted to
      the Supercopa 1998.  Vasco da Gama are admitted for the first time
      in recognition of their winning a South American Club Championship
      in Santiago in 1948.
      Argentinos Juniors were not admitted to this year's edition, 
      presumably due to finishing last in the three-team first round
      group in the 1996 Supercopa.

